        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 5:09PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 508 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Council, or 16 miles east of Whiteville, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Waccamaw, Sandyfield, Council, Bolton, and East Arcadia.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
